                            <comment id="13410" author="drmills" created="Tue, 31 May 2005 23:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The solution to this would seem to be to replace the relative locations with a reference to $&lt;/p&gt;
{spring.root}
&lt;p&gt;. My only query being if the db build is ever executed in isolation in which case spring.root will need to be defined as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13411" author="drmills" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2005 00:02:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@@ -15 +15 @@&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;../../../lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
+				&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;$
{spring.root}/lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -42 +42 @@&lt;br/&gt;
-				&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;../../../lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
+				&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;${spring.root}
&lt;p&gt;/lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -116 +116 @@&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;../../../lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
+				&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;$
{spring.root}/lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -142 +142 @@&lt;br/&gt;
-				&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;../../../lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
+				&amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;${spring.root}
&lt;p&gt;/lib&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13465" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2005 21:17:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the suggestion! PetClinic&apos;s build uses $&lt;/p&gt;
{spring.root}
&lt;p&gt; everywhere now, executing the db build script in the same base directory as the main build script (to be able to use the same relative path).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
